1
00:00:08,300 --> 00:00:10,067
<i> Let go of me, you animal!</i>

2
00:00:10,200 --> 00:00:13,400
<i>That's nothing compared
to the pain of your betrayal!</i>

3
00:00:13,533 --> 00:00:14,767
<i>You turned me
into the other woman!</i>

4
00:00:14,900 --> 00:00:15,967
<i> You lied to me!</i>

5
00:00:16,100 --> 00:00:18,000
<i> All of it was a lie!</i>

6
00:00:18,133 --> 00:00:22,933
<i>I thought you loved me,
but you're just like my dad.</i>

7
00:00:23,067 --> 00:00:25,067
<i>And I cannot tolerate
what you did.</i>

8
00:00:25,200 --> 00:00:28,533
<i>That's why I decided
to let go of both of you.</i>

9
00:00:28,667 --> 00:00:30,733
<i> Why did you spread that video?</i>

10
00:00:30,867 --> 00:00:32,933
<i>You did it to ruin me,
didn't you?</i>

11
00:00:33,067 --> 00:00:34,233
<i> Why are you blaming me?</i>

12
00:00:34,400 --> 00:00:35,367
<i>If you didn't want to get fired,</i>

13
00:00:35,500 --> 00:00:37,067
<i>then you shouldn't
have done anything wrong!</i>

14
00:00:37,200 --> 00:00:39,000
<i> So that's how you see me, huh?</i>

15
00:00:40,667 --> 00:00:43,200
<i>Well, trash belongs with trash!</i>

16
00:00:43,333 --> 00:00:46,167
<i>Why don't you just apply to the
company I'm transferring to?</i>

17
00:00:46,300 --> 00:00:48,067
<i> You received the video, right?</i>

18
00:00:48,200 --> 00:00:51,333
<i>Isn't that enough reason
to reject Marj's application?</i>

19
00:00:54,233 --> 00:00:55,400
Miss Castillo,

20
00:00:55,533 --> 00:01:00,000
thank you for coming all the way
to Manila for this interview.

21
00:01:00,133 --> 00:01:02,767
I won't miss
this opportunity, Ma'am.

22
00:01:04,167 --> 00:01:08,667
Unfortunately, we can't approve
your application yet.

23
00:01:08,833 --> 00:01:12,767
We need to conduct further
background checks.

24
00:01:12,900 --> 00:01:13,967
What?

25
00:01:14,100 --> 00:01:15,300
Why?

26
00:01:15,433 --> 00:01:18,900
My character references
are complete.

27
00:01:19,033 --> 00:01:23,100
HR received a video this morning
from an anonymous source.

28
00:01:23,233 --> 00:01:26,533
It appears you were involved
with a married man.

29
00:01:26,667 --> 00:01:30,100
We need to make sure
there are no personal issues

30
00:01:30,233 --> 00:01:33,567
that could affect your work
or the company's reputation.

31
00:01:35,067 --> 00:01:38,067
Ma'am, please believe me.

32
00:01:38,200 --> 00:01:43,100
I broke up with him the moment
I found out he was married.

33
00:01:43,267 --> 00:01:46,933
Please don't judge me
just because of that video.

34
00:01:48,233 --> 00:01:51,400
Someone's trying to destroy
my reputation.

35
00:01:52,767 --> 00:01:55,300
I'm sorry, Miss Castillo.

36
00:01:55,433 --> 00:01:59,933
We'll contact you once
the verification is complete.

37
00:02:00,967 --> 00:02:03,100
Ma'am, please.

38
00:02:03,233 --> 00:02:07,233
Give me a chance
to prove myself.

39
00:02:07,367 --> 00:02:10,100
I promise I'll do my best.

40
00:02:10,233 --> 00:02:13,967
I really, really need this job.

41
00:02:14,100 --> 00:02:16,033
Ma'am,

42
00:02:16,200 --> 00:02:18,500
please have mercy on me.

43
00:02:24,733 --> 00:02:26,400
Thanks for the favor, Claire.

44
00:02:26,533 --> 00:02:29,467
I knew you wouldn't
be able to say no to me.

45
00:02:29,600 --> 00:02:32,167
How could I?

46
00:02:32,300 --> 00:02:34,367
Thanks to you,
we received a huge discount

47
00:02:34,500 --> 00:02:35,833
on our house in Santo Tomas.

48
00:02:38,233 --> 00:02:40,800
You got a huge discount
because of me.

49
00:02:40,933 --> 00:02:42,633
But still...

50
00:02:42,767 --> 00:02:44,533
You know, I kind of feel sorry
for Miss Castillo.

51
00:02:44,667 --> 00:02:47,767
She looked like
she really needed the job.

52
00:02:47,933 --> 00:02:50,767
Forget about her.
That's karma.

53
00:02:50,900 --> 00:02:53,500
Serves her right
for messing with me.

54
00:03:59,333 --> 00:04:00,533
Sir?

55
00:04:01,600 --> 00:04:03,733
Sir Pao?

56
00:04:03,867 --> 00:04:06,100
Sir?

57
00:04:06,233 --> 00:04:09,767
Sir Paolo, we're here.

58
00:04:13,100 --> 00:04:15,300
Let's pick this up later, okay?
Angel?

59
00:04:16,567 --> 00:04:18,133
Who's Angel?

60
00:04:18,267 --> 00:04:20,833
My name's Aubrey!

61
00:04:20,967 --> 00:04:21,900
Oh, right.

62
00:04:22,033 --> 00:04:23,900
Aubrey.

63
00:04:24,033 --> 00:04:26,400
I just think of you as an angel.

64
00:04:26,533 --> 00:04:29,167
I feel like I'm in heaven
whenever I'm with you.

65
00:04:30,967 --> 00:04:34,000
Come on, don't be mad.

66
00:04:34,133 --> 00:04:36,800
I promise I'll make it up
to you, okay?

67
00:04:38,200 --> 00:04:41,900
See you later at the hotel.
Same time?

68
00:04:42,033 --> 00:04:45,033
Smile. You're way sexier
when you smile.

69
00:04:45,167 --> 00:04:46,533
Same time, okay?

70
00:05:00,200 --> 00:05:02,000
Oscar, you take care of her.

71
00:05:03,067 --> 00:05:05,300
Just make sure
she gets home safe.

72
00:05:18,500 --> 00:05:20,633
- Hello, Mom?
- Marj...

73
00:05:20,767 --> 00:05:22,867
how was the job interview?

74
00:05:23,000 --> 00:05:24,767
Did you get accepted?

75
00:05:24,900 --> 00:05:26,100
Yes, Mom.

76
00:05:26,233 --> 00:05:28,967
They were actually impressed
with me.

77
00:05:29,100 --> 00:05:30,667
Congratulations, sweetheart!

78
00:05:30,800 --> 00:05:33,867
I knew you'd get it.

79
00:05:34,000 --> 00:05:37,300
So does that mean

80
00:05:37,467 --> 00:05:40,100
you can already bring Jobert
and me to Manila?

81
00:05:41,833 --> 00:05:44,167
I'll let you know when, Mom.

82
00:05:44,300 --> 00:05:46,100
But not just yet.

83
00:05:48,767 --> 00:05:50,567
Why?

84
00:05:50,700 --> 00:05:52,333
Is there a problem?

85
00:05:52,467 --> 00:05:56,467
I thought everything was okay?

86
00:05:56,600 --> 00:05:59,767
I still need to process
some documents.

87
00:06:01,300 --> 00:06:03,767
And I need to find us a place
to stay.

88
00:06:05,567 --> 00:06:08,033
I'll be here
for a few more days, Mom.

89
00:06:08,200 --> 00:06:10,133
And...

90
00:06:10,267 --> 00:06:13,733
Please bear with me.
Just a little longer.

91
00:06:13,867 --> 00:06:14,733
Okay, sweetheart.

92
00:06:14,867 --> 00:06:17,967
Are you all right there
by yourself?

93
00:06:25,800 --> 00:06:27,200
Yes, Mom.

94
00:06:27,333 --> 00:06:28,567
Yes, Mom.

95
00:06:28,700 --> 00:06:30,900
Yes, I'm okay.

96
00:06:44,733 --> 00:06:46,500
Your load's probably
running out.

97
00:06:46,633 --> 00:06:48,833
I'll just call you again later.

98
00:06:51,100 --> 00:06:52,833
Okay, Mom.
Bye.

99
00:07:25,167 --> 00:07:27,500
Sir. Sir, I'm sorry.

100
00:07:27,633 --> 00:07:29,333
We'll talk later.

101
00:07:30,833 --> 00:07:33,300
How are you? Are you okay?
Did you get hurt?

102
00:07:33,433 --> 00:07:35,433
You shouldn't have done that.

103
00:07:35,567 --> 00:07:37,667
What if you got yourself
seriously hurt, too?

104
00:07:37,800 --> 00:07:40,767
I just saved your life.
And this is how you thank me?

105
00:07:42,067 --> 00:07:44,300
Thank you, Sir.

106
00:07:44,433 --> 00:07:45,667
You're welcome.

107
00:07:45,800 --> 00:07:47,033
But do me a favor.

108
00:07:47,200 --> 00:07:49,300
Let's just keep this
between us.

109
00:07:49,433 --> 00:07:50,800
I don't want any trouble.

110
00:07:50,933 --> 00:07:52,500
But if you ever need anything,

111
00:07:53,800 --> 00:07:55,500
I've got your back.

112
00:08:00,233 --> 00:08:03,400
Yes, Sir. I'll forget everything
that happened.

113
00:08:03,533 --> 00:08:07,333
But I do have one request, Sir.

114
00:08:15,067 --> 00:08:18,467
Sir, you can check my record
at my previous company.

115
00:08:18,600 --> 00:08:20,867
It's clean.
I did well there.

116
00:08:21,000 --> 00:08:23,800
My only mistake was
falling in love with a liar.

117
00:08:23,967 --> 00:08:26,567
But I didn't do anything wrong.

118
00:08:45,867 --> 00:08:49,600
You know,
you have this vibe...

119
00:08:49,733 --> 00:08:51,933
like you're the type people...

120
00:08:52,067 --> 00:08:57,000
want to protect,
serve, and rescue.

121
00:08:57,167 --> 00:09:01,267
That's probably why people
are drawn to you...

122
00:09:01,400 --> 00:09:03,200
especially married men.

123
00:09:03,333 --> 00:09:05,900
There's just something
about you.

124
00:09:07,233 --> 00:09:11,000
Sir, what does this have to do
with my application?

125
00:09:11,133 --> 00:09:13,667
Sorry, sorry, sorry!
Did I offend you?

126
00:09:13,800 --> 00:09:16,067
Sorry. Sorry,
Miss Tough Girl.

127
00:09:16,200 --> 00:09:18,233
Miss Tough Girl?

128
00:09:18,367 --> 00:09:19,733
Yeah.

129
00:09:19,867 --> 00:09:21,267
Miss Tough Girl.

130
00:09:24,000 --> 00:09:27,833
You were pretty badass
in that video HR showed me.

131
00:09:28,000 --> 00:09:30,133
I can see that you're a fighter.

132
00:09:30,267 --> 00:09:32,500
You don't give up easily.

133
00:09:32,633 --> 00:09:36,833
That's a good quality
for a strong real estate agent.

134
00:09:36,967 --> 00:09:38,033
So...

135
00:09:38,167 --> 00:09:39,467
I'll give you a chance.

136
00:09:41,800 --> 00:09:43,567
I got the job?

137
00:09:49,733 --> 00:09:51,900
On probation.

138
00:09:52,033 --> 00:09:53,400
One month.

139
00:09:54,767 --> 00:09:56,167
Thank you so much, Sir.

140
00:09:56,300 --> 00:09:59,400
I'll prove to you I'm more
than just a pretty face.

141
00:10:00,433 --> 00:10:03,433
Well, I'm counting on that.

142
00:10:03,600 --> 00:10:06,300
Because I do love being
surrounded by beautiful women.

143
00:10:08,167 --> 00:10:09,933
But as your boss,

144
00:10:10,067 --> 00:10:12,567
I expect results.

145
00:10:12,700 --> 00:10:13,867
Otherwise,

146
00:10:14,000 --> 00:10:16,033
I'll have to let you go.

147
00:10:16,167 --> 00:10:18,267
Do you understand that,
Miss Tough Girl?

148
00:10:18,400 --> 00:10:20,567
Yes, Sir.
I can handle it.

149
00:10:22,400 --> 00:10:24,067
What? What did you say?

150
00:10:25,167 --> 00:10:27,267
Sorry, Sir. I'm Bisaya.

151
00:10:27,400 --> 00:10:29,633
I just meant I can do it.

152
00:10:31,467 --> 00:10:32,733
We'll see.

153
00:10:44,200 --> 00:10:47,233
What's your secret,
Mrs. Torrecampo?

154
00:10:47,367 --> 00:10:50,800
Despite your age, you still look
young and beautiful.

155
00:10:53,867 --> 00:10:55,100
Oh, I don't have any secrets.

156
00:10:55,233 --> 00:10:58,767
I just eat healthy
and take care of myself.

157
00:10:58,900 --> 00:11:04,300
And I think it helps that
I stay busy with charity work

158
00:11:04,433 --> 00:11:08,300
and Torrecampo Realty's
projects.

159
00:11:08,467 --> 00:11:14,300
You know, helping others really
relieves stress, right, hon?

160
00:11:14,433 --> 00:11:17,833
You must be very proud
to have a wife like her,

161
00:11:17,967 --> 00:11:19,267
Mr. Torrecampo.

162
00:11:19,400 --> 00:11:20,633
Of course.

163
00:11:20,767 --> 00:11:23,633
Regina and I have been married
for almost three decades.

164
00:11:23,767 --> 00:11:28,033
We've had our challenges, but
we always face them together.

165
00:11:28,167 --> 00:11:30,400
And I can honestly say...

166
00:11:30,533 --> 00:11:32,333
she's my rock.

167
00:11:32,467 --> 00:11:34,567
She keeps me grounded.

168
00:11:34,700 --> 00:11:37,267
- Right, hon?
- Yes, that's right.

169
00:11:37,400 --> 00:11:39,867
And Greg has always been
the anchor of our family.

170
00:11:40,000 --> 00:11:45,567
He's the reason our family
is strong and happy.

171
00:11:45,733 --> 00:11:49,267
Standing by his side,
raising our family together

172
00:11:49,400 --> 00:11:53,500
has been the greatest
blessing of my life.

173
00:11:53,633 --> 00:11:55,100
That's so sweet.

174
00:11:55,233 --> 00:11:56,567
Well, I'll step aside
for a moment.

175
00:11:56,700 --> 00:11:58,800
- I just need to grab something.
- Sure.

176
00:11:58,933 --> 00:12:00,633
- Sure.
- Thank you.

177
00:12:07,267 --> 00:12:08,967
Edward, am I late?

178
00:12:10,300 --> 00:12:11,533
It's fine.

179
00:12:11,667 --> 00:12:14,400
Everyone's willing to wait
for the Golden Boy.

180
00:12:24,100 --> 00:12:26,400
Sir Paolo, Sir Edward,
please come over here.

181
00:12:26,533 --> 00:12:29,067
The whole family
will be in the next segment.

182
00:12:37,967 --> 00:12:39,300
Excuse me.

183
00:12:46,733 --> 00:12:49,733
Watch your answers, Edward.

184
00:12:49,900 --> 00:12:51,800
Don't embarrass this family.

185
00:12:51,933 --> 00:12:53,600
- Greg.
- Or better yet,

186
00:12:53,733 --> 00:12:55,500
just don't talk.

187
00:12:58,033 --> 00:12:59,500
Wait. Why me?

188
00:12:59,633 --> 00:13:01,667
Why am I the one
you're mad at, Dad?

189
00:13:01,800 --> 00:13:03,433
Shouldn't it be Paolo?

190
00:13:03,567 --> 00:13:07,400
He made everyone wait.
It's embarrassing.

191
00:13:07,533 --> 00:13:09,333
I'm late because of work!

192
00:13:10,400 --> 00:13:12,200
Work? Really?

193
00:13:12,333 --> 00:13:14,967
Or were you "working"
on another woman again?

194
00:13:15,100 --> 00:13:18,400
This is not the time
or place for argument.

195
00:13:18,533 --> 00:13:21,433
Please.
Get it together.

196
00:13:21,600 --> 00:13:24,567
At least until the
interview's over.

197
00:13:24,700 --> 00:13:25,667
Please?

198
00:13:27,100 --> 00:13:28,433
Paolo.

199
00:13:30,600 --> 00:13:33,600
They're ready.
Brian, we're set.

200
00:13:33,733 --> 00:13:35,267
Let's do this?

201
00:13:43,233 --> 00:13:44,800
Make sure you wipe
that glass properly, okay?

202
00:13:44,933 --> 00:13:46,300
Oh, by the way,
this is Weng.

203
00:13:46,600 --> 00:13:48,600
She's our new house helper
here at the mansion.

204
00:13:48,733 --> 00:13:49,967
And this is Oscar.

205
00:13:50,100 --> 00:13:52,867
He's our boss's driver.

206
00:13:53,000 --> 00:13:53,767
- Fix that.
- Weng,

207
00:13:53,900 --> 00:13:56,433
how's your first week here?

208
00:13:56,600 --> 00:13:59,933
It's okay. Still getting the
hang of things, but I'll adjust.

209
00:14:00,067 --> 00:14:03,400
But, wow, our bosses
are really famous, huh?

210
00:14:03,533 --> 00:14:06,067
Ma'am and Sir.
Their whole family.

211
00:14:06,200 --> 00:14:07,533
What I don't get is...

212
00:14:07,667 --> 00:14:12,900
why Sir Paolo and Sir Edward
don't seem to get along.

213
00:14:15,467 --> 00:14:18,100
Why, Manang?

214
00:14:18,233 --> 00:14:22,500
Weng, keep whatever you notice
inside this mansion

215
00:14:22,633 --> 00:14:25,233
to yourself, okay?

216
00:14:25,367 --> 00:14:27,600
You're still new.

217
00:14:27,733 --> 00:14:29,567
She's not wrong, though.

218
00:14:30,933 --> 00:14:32,867
When they were kids,

219
00:14:33,000 --> 00:14:35,867
Sir Edward...

220
00:14:36,000 --> 00:14:39,333
studied hard, was very
responsible, and very kind.

221
00:14:39,467 --> 00:14:41,600
But Sir Paolo was still
everyone's favorite.

222
00:14:43,400 --> 00:14:46,933
There was even one Christmas
party when Sir Edward got drunk.

223
00:14:47,067 --> 00:14:49,000
He almost punched Sir Paolo.

224
00:14:49,133 --> 00:14:52,267
Probably because he was jealous.
No one paid attention to him.

225
00:14:52,400 --> 00:14:54,067
Wait a second.

226
00:14:54,200 --> 00:14:57,100
Why didn't Ma'am Regina
fix things between them?

227
00:14:57,233 --> 00:14:58,533
Ma'am Regina?

228
00:14:58,667 --> 00:15:00,367
She doesn't really have
a say in this house.

229
00:15:00,500 --> 00:15:02,800
She just follows
whatever Sir Greg wants.

230
00:15:02,967 --> 00:15:05,000
That's enough, okay?

231
00:15:05,133 --> 00:15:07,200
Alright, alright.

232
00:15:07,333 --> 00:15:08,667
I'm going.

233
00:15:10,100 --> 00:15:12,033
And you.

234
00:15:12,167 --> 00:15:18,800
Whatever you see in this house,
just close your eyes.

235
00:15:18,933 --> 00:15:22,867
Whatever you hear,
cover your ears.

236
00:15:23,000 --> 00:15:26,167
And your mouth,
keep it shut, got it?

237
00:15:27,233 --> 00:15:29,400
Yes, Ma'am. Work.

238
00:15:36,000 --> 00:15:40,800
Oh my, Auntie, you're really
going to love it here.

239
00:15:40,933 --> 00:15:42,433
What? What did she say?

240
00:15:42,567 --> 00:15:44,267
I can't understand you, dear.
What did you say?

241
00:15:44,400 --> 00:15:47,000
I don't think I understood.

242
00:15:47,133 --> 00:15:49,733
Come on, Auntie.

243
00:15:51,567 --> 00:15:52,967
Look.

244
00:15:56,467 --> 00:15:58,233
- Hello.
- Hello.

245
00:15:58,900 --> 00:16:01,300
- Come in.
- Hey, you're moving in today?

246
00:16:01,433 --> 00:16:02,500
There's coffee over here.

247
00:16:05,567 --> 00:16:07,300
Welcome, welcome!

248
00:16:07,433 --> 00:16:10,067
This is it. Our home sweet home.

249
00:16:12,433 --> 00:16:15,767
Mom, we got this
apartment cheap.

250
00:16:15,900 --> 00:16:18,500
And Hannah and I
are splitting the rent.

251
00:16:18,633 --> 00:16:22,333
Sorry, it's small,
but it's a quiet neighborhood.

252
00:16:22,467 --> 00:16:24,167
Stop it. This place is fine.

253
00:16:24,300 --> 00:16:27,100
Better than forcing
ourselves to stay with Hilda.

254
00:16:27,233 --> 00:16:30,167
What matters most
is we're together now.

255
00:16:34,233 --> 00:16:36,100
Jobert, are you okay?

256
00:16:38,933 --> 00:16:41,067
I'm okay.

257
00:16:41,200 --> 00:16:43,700
It's like turtles.

258
00:16:43,867 --> 00:16:46,533
Like, when you move
into a new place,

259
00:16:48,333 --> 00:16:49,667
it takes time to adjust,

260
00:16:50,700 --> 00:16:52,867
but eventually it's okay.

261
00:16:54,133 --> 00:16:56,800
Like us. New house.

262
00:16:56,933 --> 00:17:01,433
Don't worry. I promise
we won't stay here forever.

263
00:17:01,567 --> 00:17:05,467
I'll work hard
so we can get our dream house.

264
00:17:05,600 --> 00:17:09,700
But for now, this is
where we'll stay, okay?

265
00:17:11,733 --> 00:17:14,133
Okay, Pong.

266
00:17:16,633 --> 00:17:17,633
Okay, Pong.

267
00:17:33,700 --> 00:17:34,667
Oh, dude!

268
00:17:34,800 --> 00:17:36,100
What are you doing here?

269
00:17:36,233 --> 00:17:37,300
You need something from me?

270
00:17:39,067 --> 00:17:40,767
Did you forget?

271
00:17:40,900 --> 00:17:42,133
Didn't I set up
a meeting with you

272
00:17:42,267 --> 00:17:43,933
to talk about
the Sutherland account?

273
00:17:46,433 --> 00:17:47,733
Really?

274
00:17:47,900 --> 00:17:50,267
Wait, are you still wearing
what you had on last night?

275
00:17:53,400 --> 00:17:55,033
Yeah.

276
00:17:55,167 --> 00:17:57,733
The party ended really late.

277
00:17:57,867 --> 00:18:01,800
So I crashed
at a new friend's place.

278
00:18:03,633 --> 00:18:04,933
You know what, dude?

279
00:18:07,167 --> 00:18:11,233
She was really friendly.

280
00:18:12,667 --> 00:18:15,333
We got to know
each other better.

281
00:18:15,467 --> 00:18:17,167
We totally lost track of time.

282
00:18:17,300 --> 00:18:19,767
Next thing I know, dude,
the sun was already up.

283
00:18:19,900 --> 00:18:22,467
Please, please, please, Paolo.
I'm not interested.

284
00:18:22,633 --> 00:18:24,267
Why?

285
00:18:24,400 --> 00:18:25,733
I came here to tell you

286
00:18:25,867 --> 00:18:28,467
I'm meeting Mr. and Mrs.
Sutherland later today.

287
00:18:37,000 --> 00:18:38,433
No, thank you.

288
00:18:47,033 --> 00:18:47,967
Dude...

289
00:18:49,133 --> 00:18:50,500
I'll be honest with you.

290
00:18:52,100 --> 00:18:54,600
Dad's kind of reluctant
to give you the account.

291
00:18:55,900 --> 00:18:57,100
What?

292
00:18:57,233 --> 00:19:00,067
Paolo, I can do this.
I assure you.

293
00:19:00,200 --> 00:19:01,533
You just need to trust me.

294
00:19:01,667 --> 00:19:03,400
I'll close this deal.

295
00:19:03,533 --> 00:19:05,600
I'll convince
Mr. and Mrs. Sutherland

296
00:19:05,733 --> 00:19:08,633
to make us
their exclusive realtors.

297
00:19:08,767 --> 00:19:10,567
Come on, Paolo. I can do this.

298
00:19:10,700 --> 00:19:12,933
Okay, okay, fine.

299
00:19:13,067 --> 00:19:15,700
You're making my
hangover worse.

300
00:19:15,833 --> 00:19:17,500
Sit down.

301
00:19:17,633 --> 00:19:19,400
But I'm giving
you a teammate.

302
00:19:19,533 --> 00:19:21,067
You're working as a pair.

303
00:19:21,200 --> 00:19:22,567
Who?

304
00:19:24,933 --> 00:19:26,633
Miss Tough Girl.

305
00:19:26,767 --> 00:19:27,767
Excuse me, Sir.

306
00:19:27,900 --> 00:19:29,900
I just need to have
a listing agreement signed.

307
00:19:30,067 --> 00:19:31,933
Later.

308
00:19:32,067 --> 00:19:34,033
- Perfect timing.
- Hello, Sir.

309
00:19:35,733 --> 00:19:37,867
Please meet my younger brother.

310
00:19:40,500 --> 00:19:43,567
The more serious version of me.

311
00:19:43,700 --> 00:19:44,600
Edward.

312
00:19:44,733 --> 00:19:47,867
Edward,
this is our newest agent.

313
00:19:49,233 --> 00:19:50,533
Miss Marj.

314
00:19:50,667 --> 00:19:52,467
Also known as Miss Tough Girl.

315
00:19:54,400 --> 00:19:56,267
Hello, Sir Edward.

316
00:20:00,633 --> 00:20:03,167
Oh, Miss Marj, congratulations.

317
00:20:03,333 --> 00:20:05,933
You got your first assignment.
Okay?

318
00:20:06,067 --> 00:20:08,300
You'll be teaming up
with my brother.

319
00:20:10,500 --> 00:20:11,867
Miss Marj,

320
00:20:12,000 --> 00:20:16,233
rub off some of that courage
on him, that confidence, too.

321
00:20:16,367 --> 00:20:18,000
Remember, we have a deal.

322
00:20:18,133 --> 00:20:20,300
You need to close this sale.

323
00:20:20,433 --> 00:20:21,633
Or else...

324
00:20:21,767 --> 00:20:23,633
bye-bye.

325
00:20:23,767 --> 00:20:25,067
Okay?

326
00:20:31,367 --> 00:20:33,733
-I'll just come back later, Sir.
- No, wait here.

327
00:20:35,433 --> 00:20:37,800
Yes, Jobert. Just promise me
you'll behave, okay?

328
00:20:38,767 --> 00:20:41,233
All right, we'll talk later.
I'm still at work.

329
00:20:41,367 --> 00:20:43,100
I'll call you again. Okay.

330
00:20:43,233 --> 00:20:44,833
I love you. Bye.

331
00:20:47,067 --> 00:20:49,700
Sorry, Sir. My brother called.

332
00:20:49,833 --> 00:20:51,467
It's okay.

333
00:20:51,600 --> 00:20:54,067
You're really close
with your sibling, huh?

334
00:20:54,200 --> 00:20:56,433
Yes, Sir.
Ever since we were kids.

335
00:20:56,567 --> 00:20:58,733
I'm sure you and Sir Paolo
are the same.

336
00:21:01,833 --> 00:21:04,367
Paolo and I were close
when we were younger.

337
00:21:04,500 --> 00:21:06,500
But as we grew up,

338
00:21:06,633 --> 00:21:09,133
our interests changed,
so...

339
00:21:09,300 --> 00:21:10,600
we drifted apart.

340
00:21:12,000 --> 00:21:13,833
Maybe you just need to spend
more time together.

341
00:21:13,967 --> 00:21:17,000
If you do that,
the closeness will come back.

342
00:21:21,900 --> 00:21:25,933
Marj, I hope Mr. Sutherland
likes the property.

343
00:21:26,067 --> 00:21:28,967
You don't think they'll
get bored on the tour, do you?

344
00:21:29,100 --> 00:21:32,533
Are we all set?
Did we forget anything?

345
00:21:32,667 --> 00:21:34,800
Sir, are you okay?
Are you nervous?

346
00:21:36,333 --> 00:21:38,700
Aren't you feeling pressured,
too, Marj?

347
00:21:38,833 --> 00:21:40,500
Didn't Paolo say

348
00:21:40,633 --> 00:21:44,067
this decides whether you stay
with the company?

349
00:21:44,233 --> 00:21:46,067
Of course, I'm pressured.

350
00:21:46,200 --> 00:21:50,533
But I don't want fear
to beat me, Sir Edward.

351
00:21:50,667 --> 00:21:53,300
Do you know my technique
with clients?

352
00:21:54,767 --> 00:21:56,433
I imagine they're friends.

353
00:21:56,567 --> 00:21:58,600
Friends who are visiting
our place.

354
00:21:58,733 --> 00:22:01,867
So they feel our warmth
and sincerity.

355
00:22:05,833 --> 00:22:07,200
Thank you, Marj.

356
00:22:07,333 --> 00:22:08,567
I'll remember that.

357
00:22:08,700 --> 00:22:11,233
Don't worry. I'm here.

358
00:22:11,367 --> 00:22:12,533
We're partners, right?

359
00:22:12,667 --> 00:22:15,900
I've got your back
if anything goes wrong.

360
00:22:16,067 --> 00:22:17,833
We can do this, Sir.

361
00:22:20,400 --> 00:22:21,700
We've got this.

362
00:22:34,667 --> 00:22:36,367
Hi, Mr. Sutherland.

363
00:22:36,500 --> 00:22:38,667
Mrs. Sutherland,
I'm Edward Torrecampo,

364
00:22:38,800 --> 00:22:40,933
and this is my associate, Marj.

365
00:22:41,067 --> 00:22:41,733
Hello, Edward.

366
00:22:41,867 --> 00:22:42,900
- Nice to meet you.
- Marj.

367
00:22:43,033 --> 00:22:44,700
- Hi.
- Nice to meet you, Ma'am.

368
00:22:57,933 --> 00:23:00,500
The master bedroom is one of the
highlights of the property.

369
00:23:00,633 --> 00:23:03,600
It has natural lighting
and great ventilation.

370
00:23:03,733 --> 00:23:06,367
Perfect for morning coffee
or quiet moments.

371
00:23:07,567 --> 00:23:09,200
But what about privacy?

372
00:23:09,333 --> 00:23:10,533
With all this glass,

373
00:23:10,667 --> 00:23:12,633
aren't you exposed
to the neighbors?

374
00:23:12,767 --> 00:23:15,767
The glass is treated
with high-quality tint.

375
00:23:15,900 --> 00:23:19,267
You can see out, but people
outside can't see in.

376
00:23:19,400 --> 00:23:21,567
And if you want
more shade or privacy,

377
00:23:21,700 --> 00:23:24,700
we can install
motorized blackout blinds.

378
00:23:25,767 --> 00:23:27,467
I'll be frank.

379
00:23:27,600 --> 00:23:30,500
We're looking for something
with more...

380
00:23:30,633 --> 00:23:32,800
character.

381
00:23:35,100 --> 00:23:37,733
Something that
feels lived in.

382
00:23:37,867 --> 00:23:39,967
This feels more
like a showroom.

383
00:23:40,100 --> 00:23:41,767
It's beautiful, no question.

384
00:23:41,900 --> 00:23:44,433
But it's just not for us.

385
00:23:47,133 --> 00:23:50,233
You've both been wonderful,
though.

386
00:23:50,367 --> 00:23:52,133
Your presentation was great,

387
00:23:52,267 --> 00:23:55,200
but my husband is looking
for something different.

388
00:23:55,367 --> 00:23:57,067
Sorry.

389
00:23:57,200 --> 00:23:58,633
Sir, excuse me.

390
00:23:58,767 --> 00:24:01,467
Maybe you'd consider
partnering with us?

391
00:24:01,600 --> 00:24:03,167
We could be
your exclusive realtors

392
00:24:03,300 --> 00:24:04,633
for selling
your office buildings.

393
00:24:04,767 --> 00:24:05,967
But how?

394
00:24:06,100 --> 00:24:07,933
I wasn't at all impressed
with you today.

395
00:24:09,267 --> 00:24:11,000
I may have to pull
out of the deal.

396
00:24:15,333 --> 00:24:16,967
Sorry to hear that.

397
00:24:17,100 --> 00:24:18,967
- Thank you for your time, Sir.
- Yeah.

398
00:24:23,300 --> 00:24:24,433
Mom?

399
00:24:24,567 --> 00:24:28,167
We're done here.

400
00:24:30,233 --> 00:24:32,367
She's speaking Visayan.

401
00:24:32,500 --> 00:24:34,600
Marj, what are
you going to do?

402
00:24:34,733 --> 00:24:37,800
Please don't forget.
Don't let the kids stay sweaty.

403
00:24:37,933 --> 00:24:39,000
They might catch a cold.

404
00:24:39,133 --> 00:24:42,067
Sir Edward, we don't
give up that easily.

405
00:24:42,200 --> 00:24:44,367
Just trust me. I've got this.

406
00:24:46,933 --> 00:24:49,667
Don't let the kids stay sweaty.
They might catch a cold.

407
00:24:49,800 --> 00:24:51,900
I have to go, Ma'am.
I'm still busy.

408
00:24:52,033 --> 00:24:53,767
Bye-bye.

409
00:24:53,900 --> 00:24:55,833
Ma'am. Ma'am.

410
00:25:01,700 --> 00:25:03,600
Ma'am. Ma'am.

411
00:25:05,433 --> 00:25:07,500
So, you're Bisaya?
I heard earlier.

412
00:25:07,633 --> 00:25:09,400
Oh, yeah. How about you?

413
00:25:09,533 --> 00:25:10,867
Yes, Ma'am. I'm from Cebu.

414
00:25:11,000 --> 00:25:13,867
Lapu-lapu actually.
I grew up in Lapu-lapu.

415
00:25:14,000 --> 00:25:16,033
I'm from Talisay.

416
00:25:16,167 --> 00:25:17,733
Really?

417
00:25:17,867 --> 00:25:19,800
Small world.

418
00:25:19,933 --> 00:25:22,733
I heard you talking to your mom.

419
00:25:22,867 --> 00:25:25,633
You're really worried
about your kids, huh?

420
00:25:25,767 --> 00:25:27,200
Of course.

421
00:25:27,333 --> 00:25:29,667
Even when we're out or at work,

422
00:25:29,800 --> 00:25:32,200
I'm always thinking
about the kids.

423
00:25:32,333 --> 00:25:33,567
Yeah, Ma'am.

424
00:25:33,700 --> 00:25:34,700
I feel the same way
about my brother,

425
00:25:34,833 --> 00:25:35,933
who has special needs.

426
00:25:36,100 --> 00:25:40,933
I help my mom
take care of him.

427
00:25:41,067 --> 00:25:43,300
Maybe it's just in us, Bisaya,

428
00:25:43,433 --> 00:25:45,600
to be really caring
toward our family.

429
00:25:47,233 --> 00:25:48,133
You know what, Ma'am?

430
00:25:48,267 --> 00:25:51,000
This house is perfect for you.

431
00:25:51,133 --> 00:25:54,767
The surroundings are
bright and clean.

432
00:25:54,900 --> 00:25:56,233
It's family-friendly. Safe.

433
00:25:56,367 --> 00:25:58,867
Even when you're at work,

434
00:25:59,000 --> 00:26:02,000
you're confident that
they're comfortable and safe.

435
00:26:09,767 --> 00:26:15,233
Maybe you can convince
your husband to change his mind.

436
00:26:50,000 --> 00:26:54,867
Your new agent is impressive and
very charming, Mr. Torrecampo.

437
00:26:55,000 --> 00:26:57,600
She connects with people easily.

438
00:26:57,733 --> 00:27:00,567
I can really feel her sincerity.

439
00:27:00,700 --> 00:27:04,467
She's not just after
the commission.

440
00:27:04,600 --> 00:27:07,733
Thank you very much,
Mrs. Sutherland.

441
00:27:07,867 --> 00:27:11,333
And I'm glad you had a good
experience with Miss Castillo.

442
00:27:13,733 --> 00:27:16,833
Honestly, if I were you,
I wouldn't let her go.

443
00:27:17,900 --> 00:27:19,267
Yes.

444
00:27:19,400 --> 00:27:22,867
She seems like she'll be a great
asset to the company and to me.

445
00:27:23,000 --> 00:27:24,700
Last page, Sir.

446
00:27:25,800 --> 00:27:26,967
Appreciate it.

447
00:27:27,100 --> 00:27:28,467
Thank you.

448
00:27:33,000 --> 00:27:35,933
- Thank you.
- Honey, everything okay?

449
00:27:36,067 --> 00:27:37,367
Yes.

450
00:27:44,333 --> 00:27:45,967
I'm assigning you
to a new project.

451
00:27:46,100 --> 00:27:48,633
My dad's college friend,
Mr. Valderama.

452
00:27:48,800 --> 00:27:50,467
How are you
supposed to close a deal

453
00:27:50,600 --> 00:27:52,367
looking like an old maid
in that long skirt?

454
00:27:52,500 --> 00:27:53,267
Fix yourself.

455
00:27:53,400 --> 00:27:54,600
Make sure
you don't mess this up.

456
00:27:54,733 --> 00:27:57,067
Don't worry.
I'll do my best, Sir.

457
00:27:57,200 --> 00:27:59,833
In our business,
the client is king!

458
00:27:59,967 --> 00:28:01,600
There's something
else I want.

459
00:28:01,733 --> 00:28:03,900
Excuse me. I just need to grab
something upstairs.

460
00:28:06,633 --> 00:28:08,233
You pig!

461
00:28:08,367 --> 00:28:11,200
I came here to do business,
not to be assaulted!

462
00:28:11,333 --> 00:28:12,867
Don't twist this around!

463
00:28:13,000 --> 00:28:13,933
Stop it!

464
00:28:14,067 --> 00:28:16,000
I'm the one who
was sexually assaulted here.

465
00:28:16,133 --> 00:28:17,967
Shouldn't you be protecting me?

466
00:28:18,100 --> 00:28:21,233
Let's file charges and drag
your boss into it, too!

467
00:28:21,367 --> 00:28:22,667
What?

468
00:28:25,833 --> 00:28:27,333
You're fired!
